#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SEIS_ct.rst:2
#: 7cf09cfda41646b8b966a7f3c224f56e
msgid "SEIS_ct"
msgstr "SEIS  ct (简体中文)."

#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SEIS_ct.rst:4
#: d26efe5ea6934be98cf6fbf6f1b50d9f
msgid ""
"The SEIS_ct Model assumes that infection spreads only through links between "
"neighboring nodes in a graph :math:`G=(V,E)`. Each node is in one of three "
"states: :math:`S` (susceptible), :math:`E` (exposed/incubating), or "
":math:`I` (infected). Compared with the discrete-step SEIS, **SEIS_ct uses "
"elapsed-time–dependent transition probabilities** for :math:`E\\to I` and "
":math:`I\\to S` based on the time since the last state entry."
msgstr ""
"SEIS ct模型假设感染只通过相邻的节点之间的联系在图:`G=(V,E)'中传播。 每个节点在三个州中之一: \" S \" (疑似), \" E "
"\" (暴露/孵化),或 \" I \" (感染)。 与离散步骤SEIS相比,**SEIS "
"ct基于自上次进入国家以来的时间,使用过时的依赖性过渡概率**:math:`E\\to I ' 和:math:`I\\to S ' 。"

